s activities for financial benefits. In this section we will analyze the security and privacy challenges of big data in each of the three phases of its lifecycle: i) big data acquisition, ii) big data storage, iii) big data analytics."), mdx("h2", null, "Big data acquisition"), mdx("p", null, "Big data is acquired from different sources and media via online services and business transactions, where some are structured, but many are unstructured, and semi structured including real-time processed data. We have identified key challenges in this phase that are mapped to the prominent Vs of big data as follows:"), mdx("ul", null, mdx("li", {
